<ide_selection>The user selected the lines 3010 to 3010 from /home/cboos/Workspace/github/claude-code-log/claude_code_log/renderer.py:
_reorder_paired_messages

This may or may not be related to the current task.</ide_selection>

I think there's some progress: in the first screenshot, we see task A and B having a correct number of messages, and their fold/unfold buttons will indeed lead to the correct folding/unfolding of the right messages they "contain".
However, you can see, both on the first and on the second screenshot that the sub messages are still grouped in one contiguous sequence after Task B.
So, essentially as what you presented as "Before" is still the current situation.
However, in contrast with your first attempt, there's no adverse side-effect seen in this attempt. The code changes also look good to me: adding agentId, even _reorder_sidechain_messages looks like it *should* work.
So, it's just a matter of debugging. I'd say it's called too early, in _process_messages_loop, whereas the pairing that will move the Task tool result back (immediately next to the Task tool use) happens later in _reorder_paired_messages.
